issue.title: [Bug] Fix Spelling and Grammar Mistakes in README.md
issue.body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues (including the closed ones)

### Description

After reading the README.md file, I found some spelling and grammar errors. These might make the README.md file less engaging


### Steps to reproduce

1.) Go to the repository link
2.) Find the README.md file or scroll down in the repository section in GitHub

### Expected behavior

There should be no spelling and grammar errors in the README.md file
![Screenshot from 2023-10-25 21-44-34](https://github.com/mucommander/mucommander/assets/98935619/12d82fff-fb3f-4d21-aeac-efd32a740724)


### Actual behavior

There are spelling and grammar errors in the README.md file

### Screenshots?

![Screenshot from 2023-10-25 21-44-34](https://github.com/mucommander/mucommander/assets/98935619/d768f55a-12aa-469f-9ba1-e79d61e72354)


in the last paragraph, the 'translation' spelling is wrong

### muCommander version

muCommander version 1.4.0

### Java version

JDK 17

### Operating System type and version

Ubuntu 22.04

```shell
None
```
